      • update

        public void update(long millisElapsed)
        Description copied from interface: IUpdatable
        Updates the state of the object. Any code that should be called 60 times a second should be added to this method. For example, you could update your object's position. The argument millisElapsed is the number of milliseconds that has passed since the last call to update(). You can use this to scale your movement vector.
        Specified by:
        update in interface IUpdatable
        Overrides:
        update in class Animal
        Parameters:
        millisElapsed - the milliseconds that have passed since the last call to this method.
